==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lassitude
<hw>Las"si*tude</hw> <pr>(l⟦acr⟧s"s⟦icr⟧*t⟦umac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>lassitudo</ets>, fr. <ets>lassus</ets> faint, weary; akin
to E. <ets>late</ets>: cf. F. <ets>lassitude</ets>. See
<er>Late</er>.]</ety> <def>A condition of the body, or mind, when its
voluntary functions are performed with difficulty, and only by a strong
exertion of the will; languor; debility; weariness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The corporeal instruments of action being strained to a high pitch
. . . will soon feel a <qex>lassitude</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lasslorn</ent>⟦br⟧
